      "sector": "mobility",
      "title": "Digital travel credential at check-in and boarding",
      "summary": "Travellers move through check-in and boarding by presenting credentials from their wallet at a proximity touchpoint, instead of juggling paper documents. The airline acts as the relying party and verifies an ISO-based digital identity (Photo ID / mDL) together with IATA travel credentials such as a boarding pass and booking order. The same pattern is being demonstrated by multiple airlines and airports (e.g. Air New Zealand, British Airways, Japan Airlines, IndiGo, Hong Kong and Bengaluru airports), pointing to an interoperable, document-light travel journey.",
      "organizationName": "Air New Zealand",
