      "userJourney": "1) The traveller holds a Photo ID / mDL and IATA travel credentials (boarding pass, booking order) in a supported wallet.\r\n2) At check-in or the boarding gate, a proximity reader requests the relevant credentials.\r\n3) The wallet shows the request; the traveller approves the presentation by tapping or scanning.\r\n4) The airline (relying party) verifies the digital identity and travel documents over an ISO/IEC 18013-5 flow.\r\n5) The traveller proceeds without presenting paper documents, sharing only what is needed for that step.",
